<item>
            <title>[HIVE-25967] Prevent residual expressions from getting serialized in Iceberg splits</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-25967</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This hack removes residual expressions from the file scan task just before split serialization.&lt;br/&gt;
Residuals can sometime take up too much space in the payload causing Tez AM to OOM.&lt;br/&gt;
Unfortunately Tez AM doesn&apos;t distribute splits in a streamed way, that is, it serializes all splits for a job before sending them out to executors. Some residuals may take ~ 1 MB in memory, multiplied with thousands of split&#160;could kill the Tez AM JVM.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Until the streamed split distribution is implemented we will kick residuals out of the split.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
